implying : if the trend spreads, most cars will have stickers. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caledhontelrana>Caledhon TelRana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 1589<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/23/03 2:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=896.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Shame Sentencing&quot;</span><hr size=1> I think the point is less the ability to &quot;rat them out&quot; via phone, than to shame them (as the title subtly hints) by labelling them as repeat offender drunk drivers.  And I think Shehbahn's point is that smart-ass people are going to start cranking out, buying, and using similar stickers on their vehicles just to be cute, even if they're not really drunk drivers, and once that starts happening on any significant scale, the original meaning is lost. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dantemoradis>Dante Moradis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 503<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/23/03 2:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=896.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Shame Sentencing&quot;</span><hr size=1> Even if it works on a handful of them, it's worth it.  The laws for drunk driving nationally are a friggin joke.  Honestly feel that more than one offense is inexcuseable and should be dealt with in the harshest possible manner. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:orange;font-family:comic sans ms;font-size:medium;">Dante Moradis</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
Retired from EQ - Tribunal Server<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://amishrakefight.org/gfy/">My Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=largthemiserable>Largthemiserable</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 794<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/23/03 6:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=896.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Shame Sentencing&quot;</span><hr size=1> I don't like the drunk driving laws, either, but I think this idea is exactly the wrong way to change the laws OR change the behavior of the drivers involved.  Do you really think some imbred hick is going to stop DUI'ing in his pickup truck because he has a sticker saying &quot;How's My Driving?  xxx-xxx-xxxx&quot;?  <br>
<br>
If you have a problem with the laws, fix it by getting your representative to work on changing the law.  DON'T give license to the judicial branch to change it themselves, even if the solution is a good one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tuwene>Tuwene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beware the paladin<br>with a map & a plan</span><br>  Posts: 1008<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/23/03 8:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=896.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Shame Sentencing&quot;</span><hr size=1> On a side note, I was driving through Newark, NJ a few years back (its a shithole, but I was on the way to the airport) and saw that they'd put up giant billboards all along the main drag toward the airport (heavy traffic, lots of lights).<br>
<br>
On each was a picture of someone's face, along with text, saying something like:<br>
<br>
&quot;Joe Smith.  Convicted, June 7, 2003 for soliciting prostitution.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tell the entire community about your humiliating little crimes like hiring a hooker and buying pot... its a matter of public record, of course, so entirely legal (once convicted)... but do you think it's a deterrent?<br>
<br>
I sure as hell wasn't about to jaywalk in Newark to find out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=soprena>Soprena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 713<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/24/03 2:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=896.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Shame Sentencing&quot;</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I don't like the drunk driving laws, either, but I think this idea is exactly the wrong way to change the laws OR change the behavior of the drivers involved. <br>
<br>
Do you really think some imbred hick is going to stop DUI'ing in his pickup truck because he has a sticker saying &quot;How's My Driving? xxx-xxx-xxxx&quot;? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
First off, this isn't about changing the drunk driving laws at all. It's about judges' ability to sentance convicted criminals. The issue is, should judges be allowed to use this sentancing method.  There are no laws against it now.<br>
<br>
Second, I think that this is as least as much about deterring the public as it is about deterring a repeat offense.  Sentancing is about punishing the offender, deterring repeat offenses from the same offender, and deterring offenses from the general public.  Someone else, contemplating such an act, might refrain if they think about the prospect of that bumper sticker or that billboard.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dantemoradis>Dante Moradis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 505<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/24/03 5:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=896.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Shame Sentencing&quot;</span><hr size=1> Something should be done.  If you think MADD isn't lobbying for stricter laws, and HASN'T been doing so for a LONG time, you're sadly mistaken.  When someone can still have a fourth or fifth offense and face little more than loss of license (they'll still drive anyway), and little or no jail time.. what's the deterrent?<br>
<br>
The penalties for this kind of offense should rise STEEPLY for increased offenses.  Hell.. if someone brandishes a gun and threatens lives.. even if it's empty, they face serious jailtime.  Is a 2-ton moving object in the hands of a drunk LESS hazardous to the community?  Things are all out of whack.<br>
<br>
I think a shame-inducing sentence for first time DUI's is a GOOD thing.  Let the judges be creative.. that'll stop a horde of bumper stickers.   Hell.. I'd be all for TAX dollars paying for billboards to prevent repeat offenses of that.  Sure beats a repeated drunk driver killing a family or two.<br>
